class Solution:
    def breakPalindrome(self, palindrome: str) -> str:
        n = len(palindrome)
        if n == 1:
            return ""

        # Convert the string to a list to allow modification
        pal_list = list(palindrome)

        # Try to change the first non-'a' character to 'a'
        for i in range(n // 2):
            if pal_list[i] != 'a':
                pal_list[i] = 'a'
                return ''.join(pal_list)

        # If all characters are 'a' or the string is odd and the middle character is the only one not changed
        # Change the last character to 'b'
        pal_list[-1] = 'b'
        return ''.join(pal_list)
```

This solution works by iterating through the first half of the palindromic string to find the first character that is not 'a'. Changing this character to 'a' will ensure the resulting string is lexicographically smallest and not a palindrome. If all characters in the first half are 'a', the string must be of the form "aaaa...aa" or "aaa...aa*aa...aaa" where '*' is any character. In such cases, changing the last character to 'b' will make it the smallest possible non-palindrome.
